<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1515,1720]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,451,1587,1612]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">General distribution.</emphasis>
Holomediterranean, extending to Central Europe, Middle East and Central Asia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1623,1648]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Comment.</emphasis>
This is a very variable species. The nominate form lives in Western Europe and Maghreb; the form 
<emphasis box="[151,268,1660,1684]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">brevicollis</emphasis>
Ferrari (= 
<emphasis box="[396,522,1660,1684]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">hungaricus</emphasis>
Horváth) is an East European and Asian taxon. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1109,1161,1660,1684]" name="Italy" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1174,1263,1660,1684]" name="France" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Corsica</collectingCountry>
, Sardegna, and Sicily intermediates exist (
